<span id="freeTextContainer14186230774255006041">Read the <a href='http://www.stopsmilingonline.com/story_detail.php?id=1208' rel='nofollow noopener'>STOP SMILING interview</a> with author Jane Mayer<br/><br/>Lift Every Voice<br/>By James Hughes<br/><br/>(This interview originally appeared in the third annual <a href='http://www.stopsmilingstore.com/issue3820interviews.aspx' rel='nofollow noopener'>STOP SMILING <i>20 Interviews</i> Issue</a>)<br/><br/>After millions embraced Barack Obama on election night in Chicago, though still weeks before the record crowds that flooded the National Mall and its tributaries became flyover country for a departing president bound for Dallas dormancy, I spoke with author Jane Mayer about the range of emotions and challenges churned up in </span>
  <span id="freeText14186230774255006041" style="display:none">Read the <a href="http://www.stopsmilingonline.com/story_detail.php?id=1208" rel="nofollow noopener">STOP SMILING interview</a> with author Jane Mayer<br /><br />Lift Every Voice<br />By James Hughes<br /><br />(This interview originally appeared in the third annual <a href="http://www.stopsmilingstore.com/issue3820interviews.aspx" rel="nofollow noopener">STOP SMILING <i>20 Interviews</i> Issue</a>)<br /><br />After millions embraced Barack Obama on election night in Chicago, though still weeks before the record crowds that flooded the National Mall and its tributaries became flyover country for a departing president bound for Dallas dormancy, I spoke with author Jane Mayer about the range of emotions and challenges churned up in her startling account of detainee abuse under the Bush administration, The Dark Side: The Inside Story of How the War on Terror Turned into a War on American Ideals (Doubleday).<br /><br />“I’m glad you had the time to read all those happy chapters,” Mayer says with equal parts consolation and self-deprecation. “Was it depressing?” Though the material is not for the faint of heart, her reporting in the book contributes vital information to the national conversation about our government’s stance on torture, and provokes essential questions about how to challenge violators of the Geneva Conventions.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.stopsmilingonline.com/story_detail.php?id=1208" rel="nofollow noopener">Read the complete interview...</a><br /></span>
